  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">World Small Hydropower Development Report 2019 and the knowledge platform www.smallhydroworld.org</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">UNIDO, together with the International Centre on Small Hydro Power (ICSHP) of the Ministry of Water Resources, China, have successfully launched the World Small Hydropower Development Report 2013 and subsequently the World Small Hydropower Development Report 2016 as well as the knowledge platform www.smallhydroworld.org. UNIDO and ICSHP as the small hydropower (SHP) knowledge leaders of this flagship Report are proposing to continue this partnership for the third edition:  World Small Hydropower Development Report 2019 (WSHPDR 2019), as well as providing assistance to maintain, expand and promote the said Report and Knowledge Platform.

The content of the Report contains regional overviews and country-level chapters on SHP capacity, potential, legislation and barriers to development. The WSHPDR 2019 contains over an impressive of 20 regional and 165 country chapters. These laborious and arduous research and editorial efforts have been made possible thanks to over 60 voluntary cost-free SHP experts and institutions that have contributed since 2011.

The first phase of the project (2013) has focused on establishing the branding of WSHPDR and introducing UNIDO and ICSHP as the co-publishers; while the second phase of the project (2016) has further strengthen the branding with richer content and promote usability of the knowledge platform. For this third phase (to be launched in 2019), it will be strategically aimed at promotion in terms of reaching key policymakers to all countries, with focus on UNIDO member states and developing countries with rich SHP resources, academicians and experts through international hydropower related conferences and seminars. It is aimed that the future editions will incorporate more features to make it more user-friendly.</narrative>
  </description>
